# Modal Component Usage

**ALWAYS** use the standardized `Modal.astro` component for modal/dialog overlays instead of creating custom implementations.

## Correct Pattern

```astro
import Modal from "../components/ui/Modal.astro";

<Modal id="my-modal" zIndex={10000} blurAmount="md" opacity="50">
  <div class="relative mx-auto mt-20 p-5 w-11/12 max-w-2xl bg-white dark:bg-gray-800 rounded-lg shadow-lg pointer-events-auto">
    <!-- Your modal content here -->
    <h2>Modal Title</h2>
    <p>Modal content...</p>
  </div>
</Modal>

<script>
  const modalBackdrop = document.getElementById("my-modal");
  const modalContent = document.getElementById("my-modal-content");
  
  function showModal() {
    modalBackdrop.classList.remove("hidden");
    modalContent.classList.remove("hidden");
  }
  
  function hideModal() {
    modalBackdrop.classList.add("hidden");
    modalContent.classList.add("hidden");
  }
</script>
```

